@startuml
title ECommerce Backend - Use Case Diagram

left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Guest" as Guest
actor "Customer" as Customer
actor "Admin" as Admin
actor "Operations" as Ops
actor "SMTP Server" as SMTP
actor "Payment Gateway Simulator" as Gateway

Admin --|> Customer

rectangle "ECommerce Backend API" {
  usecase "Register account" as UC_Register
  usecase "Login and receive JWT" as UC_Login
  usecase "Browse catalog" as UC_Browse
  usecase "View product feedback" as UC_ViewFeedback

  usecase "Manage own profile" as UC_Profile
  usecase "Change password" as UC_Password
  usecase "Manage addresses" as UC_Address
  usecase "Manage cart" as UC_Cart
  usecase "Place order" as UC_Order
  usecase "Pay order" as UC_Pay
  usecase "View own orders" as UC_ViewOrders
  usecase "Request cancellation" as UC_CancelRequest
  usecase "Submit product feedback" as UC_SubmitFeedback

  usecase "Manage customers" as UC_Customers
  usecase "Manage categories" as UC_Categories
  usecase "Manage products" as UC_Products
  usecase "Update order status" as UC_OrderStatus
  usecase "Review cancellations" as UC_CancelReview
  usecase "Process refunds" as UC_Refund
  usecase "Review all feedback" as UC_AllFeedback
  usecase "Monitor logs" as UC_Logs

  usecase "Send order/cancellation/refund email" as UC_Email
  usecase "Simulate online payment/refund" as UC_Gateway
}

Guest --> UC_Register
Guest --> UC_Login
Guest --> UC_Browse
Guest --> UC_ViewFeedback

Customer --> UC_Profile
Customer --> UC_Password
Customer --> UC_Address
Customer --> UC_Cart
Customer --> UC_Order
Customer --> UC_Pay
Customer --> UC_ViewOrders
Customer --> UC_CancelRequest
Customer --> UC_SubmitFeedback

Admin --> UC_Customers
Admin --> UC_Categories
Admin --> UC_Products
Admin --> UC_OrderStatus
Admin --> UC_CancelReview
Admin --> UC_Refund
Admin --> UC_AllFeedback
Admin --> UC_Logs

Ops --> UC_Logs

UC_Order .> UC_Address : <<include>>
UC_Order .> UC_Cart : <<include>>
UC_Order .> UC_Pay : <<extend>>
UC_Pay .> UC_Gateway : <<include for non-COD>>
UC_Pay .> UC_Email : <<include on confirmation>>
UC_CancelReview .> UC_Email : <<include>>
UC_Refund .> UC_Gateway : <<include>>
UC_Refund .> UC_Email : <<include on success>>
UC_SubmitFeedback .> UC_ViewOrders : <<requires delivered purchase>>

SMTP <-- UC_Email
Gateway <-- UC_Gateway

note right of UC_Login
  JWT roles are derived from configured admin email list.
  Non-admin users can only access their own customer,
  address, and cart resources where controllers enforce it.
end note

@enduml
